Ad Text:
One of Australia's most well-known companies are looking for someone who has a consultative background and a passion for turning data into meaningful insights that drive business decisions.

As the Lead Customer Insights Analyst, you will analyse complex datasets, uncover opportunities, and provide data-driven recommendations that influence key initiatives. Your ability to bridge analytics with business strategy will be essential in delivering measurable results.  

What You'll Do

Build meaningful relationship across the business and advise senior stakeholders with the use of key insights
Identify trends, patterns, and opportunities within large datasets to optimize business performance.
Develop and implement analytical models that provide actionable insights.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand challenges and deliver data-backed solutions.
Present findings in a clear, compelling manner to stakeholders at all levels.
Evaluate and refine analytical approaches to continuously improve accuracy and effectiveness.
Mentor and support junior analysts, fostering a data-driven culture.
  What You Bring

A background in Customer or Marketing Analytics 
Any experience working in an external or internal consultancy team would be advantageous 
Strong problem-solving skills with a keen ability to translate data into strategic insights.
Ability to communicate complex findings to both technical and non-technical audiences.
Proficiency in SQL and at least one programming language for analytics (e.g., Python, R)
A proactive mindset with a focus on driving business outcomes through data.
Why This Role?   

This is an opportunity to have a direct impact by shaping data-driven strategies and influencing decision-making. If you enjoy working with data to solve real-world challenges and thrive in a collaborative environment, we'd love to hear from you.

Are you an experienced data governance professional who enjoys shaping how data is trusted, managed and used across an organisation? Do you thrive in environments where influence, clarity and practical execution matter more than formal authority?
 
We've been engaged by a well-known and highly regarded organisation to identify a Data Governance Manager to play a critical role in strengthening enterprise data trust, quality and accountability.
 
This is a role that is designed for a senior practitioner who wants to operate as the subject matter expert for data governance, working closely with business, technology and analytics teams to embed sustainable governance practices across the organisation. 
 
What you'll be doing

Designing and embedding enterprise data governance frameworks, standards and operating models
Establishing clear data ownership, stewardship and accountability across key data domains
Defining and maintaining data quality, metadata and lineage standards to support trusted decision-making
Partnering with stakeholders to translate governance principles into practical, adopted processes
Supporting regulatory, privacy and risk obligations through well-defined data controls
Advising on governance requirements for analytics, reporting and advanced data use cases
Influencing data practices and behaviours through expertise, guidance and credibility rather than direct authority
About you

Proven experience operating at a senior level in data governance, data management or data quality roles
Strong understanding of governance frameworks, data ownership models and quality management
Ability to balance rigour with pragmatism, ensuring governance enables rather than blocks outcomes
Confident stakeholder engagement skills, including with senior leaders and non-technical audiences
Experience working across complex data landscapes and federated teams
Comfortable owning governance initiatives end to end and driving adoption across the business
Why this opportunity stands out

A true hands-on governance role with the possibility of building out a team
High visibility and influence across data, analytics and technology functions
Opportunity to shape how data is trusted and used at an enterprise level
A mature organisation that recognises governance as a business enabler, not overhead
This role is ideal for a senior data governance professional who wants to drive real change, influence enterprise data practices and remain close to the work with the opportunity to build out a team.
